Enertopia Corp. Key Developments

Enertopia Corp. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended May 31, 2017
Jul 14 17
Enertopia Corp. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended May 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company has posted loss for the period before other items of $155,277 against $96,532 a year ago. Net loss and comprehensive loss for the period was $251,027 against $84,037 a year ago.

For the nine months, the company has posted loss for the period before other items of $558,834 against $375,450 a year ago. Net loss and comprehensive loss for the period was $642,269 against $388,005 a year ago. Basic and diluted loss per share was $0.01 against $0.01 a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities was $288,437 against $232,149 a year ago.


Enertopia Seeks Acquisitions
May 11 17
Enertopia Corp.(OTCPK:ENRT) recently disclosed in a corporate update, "We are excited about our findings and to bring these to fruition by deploying the
necessary capital to potential acquisitions to achieve success and to increase shareholder value."


Enertopia Corporation Provides Lithium Exploration Update
May 8 17
Enertopia Corporation announced that after six months of due diligence and internal review that it will be launching a very targeted location specific review of high priority Lithium targets across the South Western USA over a 10 day period from May 17 to May 27. The company believes this approach is in the best interests of the company and all shareholders. Any self-generated and acquired projects would not be subject to 3rd party cash payments, share issuances or over riding royalties. The company further announces that it will be conducting its first lithium exploration program in Argentina from June 1-5 after several months of due diligence and internal review targeting very specific locations with the company's Argentinian consultants. The company will be attending the Catamarca Lithium conference on June 6-7 and will be meeting with pre-selected lithium salar owners. After a complete internal project review of the company's three brine targets in Nevada the company has decided not to make its final property payment and the projects have been returned to the property vendors and the company has terminated its option agreement that it entered into on May 12, 2016.


